1 501( c)(3), whose primary focus is conducting peer-reviewed basic
2 biomedical research. The organization shall:
3 a. have a board of directors,
4 b. be able to accept grants in its own name,
5 c. be an identifiable institute that has its own
6 employees and administrative staff, and
7 d. receive at least Fifteen Million Dollars
8 ($15,000,000.00) Twenty Million Dollars
